All functions

adjust_stan_qx

Apply logit regression coefficients to logit post-standard LT qx values (and standard 45q15 and 5q0), along with input target (HIV-free, except for ZAF which is with-HIV) logit 45q15/5q0 to generate adjusted age-specific values

agg_u5_env

Aggregrate Under-5 Age Groups in the Under-5 Envelope

calc_95_no_hmd_mx

Replace 95+ death rate for envelope, in non-HMD countries, with fitted relationship between 90-94 and 95+ derived from HMD

calc_mahalanobis

Calculate Mahalanobis Function

calc_stan_lt

Calculate Standard Life Tables

gen_110_mx

Generate mx and nLx for 110 age groups based on age 105 values

gen_80plus_ax

Calculate ax for age groups Over 80

gen_stage_1_life_table

Generate initial life tables from qx values of the first-stage iteration and regression parameters (HIV-free if non-ZAF, with-HIV if ZAF)

gen_stage_2_life_table

Generate a Full Lifetable from stage-2 results, given mx, ax, and qx

gen_starting_ax

Generate Starting ax Values for Ages 10-100

gen_whiv_env

Create With-HIV Envelope Results

import_lt_empirical

Import Empirical Lifetable values based on the lifetable database category for a given country

stage_1_5q0_adjustment stage_1_45q15_adjustment with_hiv_5q0_adjustment with_hiv_45q15_adjustment hiv_free_ZAF_5q0_adjustment hiv_free_ZAF_45q15_adjustment

Functions to apply to qx iteration process.

qx_iterations

Wrapper to initialize variables for qx iteration process

recalc_85plus_qx

Recalculate over-80 qx values based on HMD VR relationships with age 80 qx

recalc_ax

Recalculate ax values to produce re-optimized qx and ax values

recalc_u10_nlx_mx_ax

Calculate under-10 nlx, mx, and ax values

rescale_hiv_cdr

Rescale HIV Crude Death Rates

select_scalars

Run the iteration process to select the best scalars for the stage 1 and 2 iterations.

smooth_stan_lts

Smooth post-standard LT matching lifetables for selected countries

subtract_hiv_mx

Subtract HIV cause-specific mx values from 45q15 and 5q0
